    <briefdescription>
<para>Base class for GUI programs in the GUI OS. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Extends <ref refid="classBasicProgram" kindref="compound">BasicProgram</ref> with rendering capabilities. Each GUI program represents an independent window/feature that can be shown/hidden and rendered independently. Programs are analogous to OS processes - they have lifecycle management, state, and can communicate via the command queue.</para>
<para>Design Philosophy:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Each program is self-contained and owns its rendering logic</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Programs communicate via commands (loose coupling)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Programs can be activated/deactivated independently</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>The <ref refid="classGuiProgramManager" kindref="compound">GuiProgramManager</ref> acts as the &quot;process scheduler&quot; </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
